List of key players mentioned in source,Not mentioned in source.,"Source describes technologies in the market as hydrometallurgical (selective leaching/solvent extraction), bioleaching using engineered microorganisms, and pyrometallurgical processes.","Permanent magnets (HDD, EV motors, wind turbines) and electronic waste streams are primary targets for the companies listed.","Claimed recovery performance in source: hydrometallurgical processes 90-95% extraction efficiency; MP Materials facility: 95% Nd/Dy recovery at 5,000 t/yr capacity; Geomega demo: 92% Nd/Pr recovery.","Mixed commercial status: several companies operating commercial-scale facilities processing thousands of tons/year; MP Materials commercial facility (5,000 t/yr); Geomega demonstration plant; others expanding capacity and pilot facilities.","Reported partnerships/customers include Umicore-BMW JV for EV motor magnet recovery, Tesla-Redwood Materials collaboration, and e-waste partnerships with Google and Microsoft.",Funding noted: Urban Mining Company EUR 45M Series B; public funding examples include US DOE ARPA-E USD 140M and broader private equity >USD 300M globally.,Recent milestones (2024): MP Materials Nevada facility completion; Umicore-BMW JV announcement; Urban Mining Series B; Geomega demo plant commissioning; Shin-Etsu USD 200M investment in Japan.
